Snack time is anytime! If you are looking for easy ways to add a boost of nutrition to your latest snack attack, fruits and veggies are the way to go. For flavorful snacking, look no further. One mango is all you need to add the amazing flavor that you’re craving at the moment. Simply slice into a juicy, ripe mango and add a few additional ingredients to make some quick and easy mango snacks. 

A ¾ cup serving of mango adds important vitamins and nutrients to a balanced diet, including 50% of the Daily Value of Vitamin C, 15% of the daily value of folate and 8% of the daily value of Vitamin A.

#mango #mangos #mmmango #alwaysmangoszn #mangoparty

https://www.mango.org/blog-beat-that-snack-attack/

When you choose a mango, don't focus on color. It is not the best indicator of ripeness.

Squeeze the mango gently. A ripe mango will give slightly. A medium-ripe mango will be somewhat firm, and an unripe mango will be very firm to the touch. Use your experience with produce such as peaches and avocados to help you easily choose a mango, since they also become softer as they ripen.

Did you know that mangos can be enjoyed at all levels of ripeness?

Bonus: How to Speed up Ripening! 

#mango #mangos #mmmangos #alwaysmangoSZN #mangoparty
